            {
               "text": "### The Origin of the Universe\n\nThe image in this section represents our understanding of the history of the universe according to the Lambda-CDM model (<htcite0>).\n\n#### Our Initial Explanations\n\nThe origin of the universe is something that humanity has been trying to explain for millennia.\n\nVarious models have been created by human beings to explain the creation of the “sky” and the Earth, many of which were centered on humanity — that is, they were anthropocentric (<htcite1>):\n- Around <htdate0>, the Babylonians described the creation of humankind in the **Epic of Atrahasis**. They also narrated a great divine punishment through a flood, from which only Atrahasis survived (<htcite2>; <htcite3>; <htcite4>; <htcite5>).\n- Although the **Popol Vuh** was written in Mesoamerica (*Abya Yala*) between <htdate1> and <htdate2> (<htcite6>), murals found in El Mirador and Izapa, dated to around <htdate3>, show that the beliefs recorded in the Popol Vuh already existed in the region long before it was written (<htcite7>).\n\nAlthough humanity created other epic texts — some influenced by these — (<htcite8>; <htcite9>), we will limit ourselves to these two in this Atlas.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a1a7c478-9061-4160-ba43-301c081733e9",
