            {
               "text": "#### What Do We Really Know?\n\nThe evolution of knowledge about the structure of the universe is relatively recent, with major advances occurring from the 20th century onward (<htcite0>), according to the Gregorian calendar.\n\nAmong the many discoveries that expanded our understanding of the cosmos, two stand out for helping us comprehend how the planet we live on was formed:\n- Edwin Hubble’s discovery that the universe is expanding (<htcite1>);\n- The discovery of the Cosmic Microwave Background Radiation, the oldest information we have ever measured from the universe (<htcite2>).\n\nThese findings are represented in the image above and will be further detailed in the upcoming texts of this section of the *Atlas*.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "2544abb0-dc03-4654-81df-298f74faa908",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Texts with Sciences (Part I)",
